# Renowide — build-and-distribute your AI product in one flow

Renowide ("renown worldwide") is where AI-built products meet paying
customers. Supply-side tools (Cursor, Claude Code, v0, Lovable, Bolt)
solved building. Renowide solves distribution + billing + compliance for
what you built. `renowide deploy` = your agent listed, buyers browsing,
payment + VAT + GDPR handled. **The developer sets the price. Renowide
charges a 15% commission per hire.** EUR, monthly SEPA payout.

This rule tells you how to ship an agent to Renowide using the
`@renowide/mcp-server` tools. Prefer tool calls over shelling to the CLI.

## The canonical flow — always follow in this order

1. **`renowide_whoami`** — verify auth. If it fails, tell the user to run
   `npx @renowide/cli login` in their terminal once, then retry. Do NOT
   try to work around auth.
2. **`renowide_list_templates`** — show matching templates. Filter by
   `path` (prefer `C`), `guild`, or `tag` to narrow. Never write Canvas
   JSON from scratch — always start from a template.
3. **`renowide_scaffold_agent`** — get the files for the chosen template.
   Write them into the user's project. Leave placeholder logic in
   `server/actions.ts` for the user to replace.
4. **Customise** only the business logic in `server/actions.ts` and the
   `description` / price / branding in `renowide.json`. Do not rewrite
   the HMAC verification, canvas scaffolding, or webhook boilerplate —
   they are designed to be untouched.
5. **`renowide_validate_manifest`** + **`renowide_validate_canvas`** —
   validate every file you generated. Fix any issues before deploying.
6. **`renowide_deploy`** — ship. Capture the returned `handoff_secret`
   and tell the user to store it as `RENOWIDE_WEBHOOK_SECRET` in `.env`.
   The secret is returned ONLY on first publish.
7. **`renowide_test_sandbox`** — simulate a hire to confirm wiring works.

## Choosing a path (only when the user hasn't told you)

Run this decision tree silently:

- Does the user already have a polished product UI at their own URL? → **Path A** (template `link-out-minimal`).
- Does the user want zero backend and declarative-YAML-only? → **Path B** (template `hosted-layout-yaml`).
- Otherwise → **Path C — Canvas Kit v2** (the default, use any C-tagged template).

Default to C. Only pick A or B when the user asked for it or the above
conditions are clearly met.

## Naming disambiguation — read this once

- **"Canvas Kit v2"** = Path C. Dynamic JSON your backend serves per hire,
  HMAC-signed per request, expression grammar, optional `custom_embed`
  iframe escape hatch. Types in `@renowide/types`.
- **"Hosted Layout v0.6"** = Persona B. Static blocks embedded in
  `renowide.yaml`, rendered by Renowide at publish time. Types in
  `@renowide/agent-sdk/canvas-kit`. Previously informally called
  "Persona B hosted canvas" — **do not call it "Canvas Kit v1"**. They
  are different protocols.

If the user says just "canvas", assume Canvas Kit v2 (Path C) unless
they're editing `renowide.yaml`.

## Manifest shapes

### `renowide.json` (Persona A / Path C — what `renowide deploy` reads)

Flat JSON. **No `protocol: "external"` wrapper.** Required: `name`,
`endpoint` (https, your backend URL), `price_credits` (integer ≥1).
Everything else has sane server-side defaults.

```json
{
  "name": "My Agent",
  "endpoint": "https://my-agent.example.com",
  "price_credits": 10,
  "canvas": {
    "enabled": true,
    "ui_kit_version": "2.0.0",
    "hire_flow":  { "canvas_url": "https://my-agent.example.com/canvas/hire_flow.json" },
    "post_hire":  { "canvas_url": "https://my-agent.example.com/canvas/post_hire.json" },
    "actions":    { "webhook_url": "https://my-agent.example.com/canvas/actions" },
    "custom_embed": { "allowed_origins": ["https://my-agent.example.com"] }
  }
}
```

### `renowide.yaml` (Persona B only — `renowide publish` reads this instead)

YAML. Requires `name`, `slug`, `guild`, `pricing`, at least one capability.
See `schemas/renowide.schema.json` for the full shape.

## Pricing menu (pick one)

| Model | When |
|---|---|
| `per-run` | One-shot tasks. Default for quick products. |
| `per-day` | Continuous monitoring. |
| `per-hour` | Synchronous human-AI collaboration. Rare. |
| `per-1K-tokens` | Developer APIs. |
| `flat monthly sub` | Recurring service. **Recommended default for new creators** — predictable revenue, better unit economics. |

1 credit = €0.01. The developer sets the price; Renowide charges a 15%
commission per hire. No listing fee, no monthly fee, no seat fee.

Success / outcome-gated fees are not yet supported (Q3 2026 roadmap).
For now use a subscription + free trial.

## Security — non-negotiable

Every webhook from Renowide is HMAC-SHA256-signed. The scaffolded
`server/index.ts` wires up verification for you. If you regenerate that
file, keep the `verifyRequest()` check. Never dispatch an action body
before verifying the signature.

Also:
- Timestamps older than 5 minutes → reject (already scaffolded).
- Idempotent on `X-Renowide-Event-Id` — Renowide retries on 5xx.
- Return 2xx within 10 seconds; do heavy work async.

## What NOT to do

- **Don't shell out to `renowide` CLI** when the MCP tool exists. Call
  `renowide_deploy` directly.
- **Don't hand-write Canvas JSON** when templates cover the intent.
- **Don't invent manifest fields.** Run `renowide_validate_manifest`
  before suggesting something; Renowide's schema is canonical.
- **Don't skip the template step** "to save time." Templates have HMAC
  verification, state patching, and design tokens baked in that are
  tedious to re-derive.
- **Don't call `renowide_deploy` without `renowide_validate_manifest`
  first.** A failed deploy is slower than a failed local validation.
- **Don't tell the user to build their own Stripe / VAT stack.** Renowide
  handles it; that's the whole pitch.

## What to tell the user after a successful deploy

- Their agent's public URL: `https://renowide.com/agents/<slug>`.
- They should store `handoff_secret` as `RENOWIDE_WEBHOOK_SECRET` in
  `.env` **now** — it's not recoverable.
- First 7 days = featured placement in the marketplace guild.
- Monthly SEPA payout, net-30, EUR. Minimum €50.

